#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:3
msgid "Towards reproducibility: pinning Nixpkgs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:5
msgid "In various Nix examples, you'll often see the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:7
msgid ""
"{ pkgs ? import <nixpkgs> {} }:\n"
"\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:14
msgid ""
"`<nixpkgs>` points to the file system path of some revision of {term}"
"`Nixpkgs`. Find more information on [lookup paths](lookup-path-tutorial) in "
"[](reading-nix-language)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:18
msgid ""
"This is a **convenient** way to quickly demonstrate a Nix expression and get "
"it working by importing Nix packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:20
msgid ""
"However, <ref-search-path>**the resulting Nix expression is not fully "
"reproducible**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:20
msgid "<ref-search-path>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:22
msgid "Pinning packages with URLs inside a Nix expression"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:24
msgid ""
"To create **fully reproducible** Nix expressions, we can pin an exact "
"version of Nixpkgs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:26
msgid ""
"The simplest way to do this is to fetch the required Nixpkgs version as a "
"tarball specified via the relevant Git commit hash:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:28
msgid ""
"{ pkgs ? import (fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/"
"archive/06278c77b5d162e62df170fec307e83f1812d94b.tar.gz\") {}\n"
"}:\n"
"\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:35
msgid ""
"Picking the commit can be done via [status.nixos.org](https://status.nixos."
"org/), which lists all the releases and the latest commit that has passed "
"all tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:38
msgid "When choosing a commit, it is recommended to follow either"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:40
msgid ""
"the **latest stable NixOS** release by using a specific version, such as "
"`nixos-21.05`, **or**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:41
msgid "the latest **unstable release** via `nixos-unstable`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:43
msgid "Next steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs.md:45
msgid ""
"For more examples and details of the different ways to pin `nixpkgs`, see "
"{ref}`ref-pinning-nixpkgs`."
msgstr ""

